<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="25" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="25">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="25">
Distinguished from the phylogenetically closely-related species, 
<taxonomicName genus="D." lsidName="D. biguttulata" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" rank="species" species="biguttulata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">D. biguttulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, by its filiform, eguttulate alpha conidia.
</paragraph>
